1
00:00:00,250 --> 00:00:02,208
Interviewer: Okay, in these 38 days

2
00:00:02,250 --> 00:00:05,166
28 days in this prison and 10 days in another prison

3
00:00:05,541 --> 00:00:09,250
How many times did you go to interrogation and to the judge?
Witness: Twice

4
00:00:11,291 --> 00:00:14,791
Interviewer: And was the judge the same both times?

5
00:00:15,875 --> 00:00:20,125
No, they were different people in each interrogation

6
00:00:20,791 --> 00:00:23,250
Interviewer: So the first interrogation happened in the hall?
Witness: Here

7
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:24,500
Interviewer: And where did the other one happen?

8
00:00:25,125 --> 00:00:27,125
It happened at the archdiocese

9
00:00:27,750 --> 00:00:29,791
Interviewer: What did he ask you about specifically at the archdiocese?

10
00:00:30,916 --> 00:00:33,291
He asked me about the matter of the medicines as well

11
00:00:34,291 --> 00:00:39,541
And as I told you, he asked me about the people present here

12
00:00:39,541 --> 00:00:42,875
Whom you know, and who was in this church

13
00:00:42,916 --> 00:00:50,541
And who the priest is, about his family, his children, and his brothers, and what you know

14
00:00:52,041 --> 00:00:55,500
And whom you know among the Christians who left

15
00:00:55,791 --> 00:00:58,000
I told him, All the Christians left—none remained

16
00:00:58,041 --> 00:01:00,250
Some remained who had converted to Islam

17
00:01:00,250 --> 00:01:02,000
Among them this Saadallah, the restaurant owner

18
00:01:02,916 --> 00:01:07,000
He converted to Islam out of fear, and stayed here

19
00:01:08,750 --> 00:01:12,375
Then he went to Baghdad and returned to his religion again

20
00:01:13,208 --> 00:01:18,875
Interviewer: Did they try to get information from you, not only about the Christians?

21
00:01:18,916 --> 00:01:22,166
But about their money, their houses, and their properties in the area

22
00:01:22,208 --> 00:01:28,000
And details about things they couldn’t know, for example

23
00:01:28,791 --> 00:01:32,208
They asked me about the graves of the Christians

24
00:01:32,625 --> 00:01:35,791
About the burial place of the priests

25
00:01:35,875 --> 00:01:37,250
I told them, In Mary Church

26
00:01:38,916 --> 00:01:42,500
The tomb is in the church in the Qasan area

27
00:01:42,625 --> 00:01:44,916
I know that because I participated with them, as they were my neighbors

28
00:01:45,250 --> 00:01:47,625
They have intelligence and information and know everything

29
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:51,916
They know what the child playing in the street is doing

30
00:01:53,625 --> 00:01:56,250
Interviewer: Were you surprised by these questions?
Witness: Yes, of course I was surprised

31
00:01:57,916 --> 00:02:00,541
Interviewer: These questions they asked you that surprised you

32
00:02:02,666 --> 00:02:06,916
What did they leave you with exactly during the interrogation?

33
00:02:06,916 --> 00:02:10,291
I became fearful, terrified

34
00:02:11,125 --> 00:02:12,791
Because they frighten people

35
00:02:14,166 --> 00:02:16,500
Interviewer: Did they use threats with you during the interrogation?

36
00:02:17,291 --> 00:02:18,666
Yes, to some extent

37
00:02:19,625 --> 00:02:20,750
Interviewer: What did he say to you, for example?

38
00:02:21,916 --> 00:02:28,333
He said, Speak, Hajj, about what you know

39
00:02:29,041 --> 00:02:30,500
Better than us asking you

40
00:02:31,125 --> 00:02:33,500
So I told them what I had

41
00:02:34,041 --> 00:02:35,541
So that they wouldn’t be the ones asking me

42
00:02:36,541 --> 00:02:39,125
Interviewer: What did he ask you specifically?

43
00:02:40,041 --> 00:02:42,750
They asked me, What is your job?

44
00:02:42,791 --> 00:02:45,500
And who comes to you, and who sits with you?

45
00:02:45,791 --> 00:02:47,250
And what do you know about ISIS

46
00:02:48,041 --> 00:02:51,500
Out of fear I told them that ISIS is good

47
00:02:52,041 --> 00:02:54,666
And there’s nothing wrong with it, and you are an Islamic state

48
00:02:55,875 --> 00:02:56,916
Things like that

49
00:02:57,875 --> 00:03:01,375
And I was terrified of them

50
00:03:01,791 --> 00:03:04,916
Interviewer: From the questions they asked you

51
00:03:05,041 --> 00:03:07,625
It appears they knew many details about you

52
00:03:07,916 --> 00:03:14,250
Did they beat you or insult you while questioning you?

53
00:03:14,291 --> 00:03:16,291
Or did any of the members standing behind you

54
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:22,666
Attempt to deal with you with a weapon or by using a sharp instrument?

55
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:25,333
Or did anything specific happen during their interrogation of you?

56
00:03:26,041 --> 00:03:28,250
No, from when they took me to Mar Yousef Church

57
00:03:28,916 --> 00:03:32,500
I overstepped a little in speaking with them

58
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,000
So one of them pushed me

59
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:37,916
And I told you when I fell on the stairs

60
00:03:37,916 --> 00:03:40,250
Because there were stairs

61
00:03:40,875 --> 00:03:43,041
This fall still affects me

62
00:03:43,041 --> 00:03:45,291
I have pain in my back and legs

63
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:50,041
Interviewer: What caused the problems during the conversation?

64
00:03:50,875 --> 00:03:52,875
Because they brought me in unjustly

65
00:03:55,125 --> 00:04:01,500
I mean, I hadn’t committed a crime to be imprisoned, or anything like that

66
00:04:02,041 --> 00:04:06,166
And I knew I had done nothing and that I was innocent

67
00:04:07,041 --> 00:04:08,791
When my imprisonment dragged on

68
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:11,791
I asked them, What is the reason for my imprisonment?

69
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:15,000
They told me, You know everything. But I didn't know anything
